row up again in the future rightly 1 might say the recluse gotama is against enjoyment but not in the way you mean and the brahman said master gautama affirms the theory of inaction and the buddha said brahmin i declare abstinence from action in respect to misconduct indeed word and thought i proclaim inaction in respect of all evil and sinful conditions rightly 1 might say the recluse gotama affirms the theory of inaction but not in the way you mean again the brahman said master gautama is an annihilationist and the buddha said brahmin i declare the cutting off of lust hatred and delusion i proclaimed the annihilation of all evil and sinful conditions rightly 1 might say that recruits gautama is an annihilationist but not in the way you mean the brahman said master gautama feels about abhorrence and the buddha said brahman i have poor misconduct indeed word and thought i applaud entertaining all evil and sinful conditions rightly 1 might say the recluse gautama feels abhorrence but not in the way you mean the brahmana said master gautama is an abolitionist and the buddha said brahman i preached the doctrine of abolishing lust hatred and delusion i teach the dhamma of abolishing all evil and sinful conditions rightly 1 may say the recruits guatemala is an abolitionist but not in the way you mean the brahmana said master gautama is given to mortification and the buddha said brahman have proclaimed that evil and sinful conditions should be mortified yes is conduct indeed word and thought verily whosoever has abandoned rooted out made like palm tree stumps has caused not to be as so conditioned that they rise not again evil and sinful conditions which should be mortified he i say is given to mortification brahman the tata gata has abandoned rooted out all such conditions rightly 1 may say the recluse gautama is given to mortification but not in the way you mean the brahmana said master gautama is against rebirth and the buddha said this is the reason brahmin by which 1 would be right in saying that recruits gotama is against rebirth verily whosoever has abandoned cut off at the root for the future descend into the womb renewed becoming and rebirth he i say is against rebirth the tatar gatherer brahmin has all done this is indeed the reason brahmin by which 1 would be right in saying the recluse gotama is against rebirth but not in the way you mean brahmin it is just as if a sitting of 8 or 10 or a dozen hens eggs were fully set upon fully warmed and fully made become and of those young chicks the 1 which before all the rest broke the eggshell with its spike claws or with its beak and hatched out safely how would you term it the oldest the the eldest or the youngest 1 would say it was the eldest master gautama certainly master gautama is the eldest of them even so brahmin when i for the sake of mankind enveloped in ignorance as it were egg born had broken the eggshell of ignorance i alone in the world was fully awake to unsurpassed and complete awakening verily brahman i was the eldest and the best in the world moreover brahmin i was resolute full of energy active upright intent and not forgetful tranquil within my being unperturbed collected and composed in mind apparently brahmin aloo from sen's desires aloo from unwholesome states i entered and abort in the first jhana which is accompanied by applied and sustained thought with delight and pleasure born of solitude with the stilling of applied and sustained thought i entered and abort in the second jhana which has internal self-confidence and singleness of mind without applied and sustained thought with delight and pleasure born of concentration with the fading away of delight i entered and aboard in the third jhana equanimous mindful and aware and i experience in my body the pleasure whereof the aryans declare the equanimous and mindful as a joyful abiding by the abandoning of bodily pleasure and bodily pain by the passing away of joy and grief i entered and abort in the fourth jhana a state of utter purity of mindfulness and equanim free of pain and pleasure with heart thus serene purified cleansed without blemish devoid of defilement supple ready to act firm and imperturbable i bend the mind so that i might know and call to mind previous lives i call to mind diverse former lives that is to say 1 birth or 2 or 3 or 4 or 5 or 10 or 20 or 30 or 40 or 50 or 100 or a thousand or 100 000 or many an age of rolling on or many an age of rolling bank or many an age of both rolling on and rolling back such 1 i was by name of such a clan of such a cast such was my food such my experience of wheel and war such was the end of my life passing away dance i arose in such a place there such was my name such my clan such my car such my food such my experience of wheel and wall such my end passing away from there i arose here thus many a previous life are called to mind with his circumstances and details this brahmin was the first knowledge attained by me in the first watch of the night ignorance being removed knowledge arose darkness being removed light arose as i abroad strenuous earnest and residue this brahmin was my first hatching like a young chicks from the eggshell with hard vaseline purified cleansed without blemish devoid of defilement supple ready to act firm and imperturbable i bend the mind so that i might discern the passing away and reappearance of beings with the deva i purified and surpassing the human eye i saw and i knew beings in course of hearing on being slowly and exalted beautiful and ugly happy and in war according to their deeds and i thought these worthies were given over to evil practices indeed word and thought will be violence of the aryans holders of wrong views men who have acquired this karma from wrong views and on the breaking up of the body after death have arisen in the untoward way the ill way the abyss hell but these good souls behave rightly indeed word and thought where no revilers of the aryans held right views and